-- LEG Immobilien raises 205 mln euros with share placement
-- By Harro ten Wolde
-- Thu Oct 09, 2014 04:15PM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, Oct 9 (Reuters) - German real estate company LEG Immobilien <LEGn.DE> said on Thursday it had raised 205 million euros ($260 million) with the placement of 4.1 million new shares.

The company, which earlier on Thursday said it had bought 9,600 residential units from Deutsche Annington <ANNGn.DE>, placed the shares at 50 euros apiece via an accelerated bookbuilding with institutional investors. LEG Immobilien shares closed at 52.02 euros on Thursday.